'''第零大道'''（{{lang-en|0 Avenue}}）是[[加拿大|加拿大]][[不列颠哥伦比亚省|不列颠哥伦比亚省]]最南端的一条东西向的道路，由西向东从[[素里|素里]]延伸至[[亞博斯福|亞博斯福]]，道路全程与[[美加边境|美加边境]]紧邻并排而行。<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.seattlepi.com/news/article/Exploring-the-border-at-Blaine-U-S-Canada-1300963.php | title = Exploring the border at Blaine: U.S.-Canada crossing offers its own tourist experience | work = Seattle Pi | date = 2009-02-25 | accessdate = 2021-02-06 | archive-date = 2021-03-25 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210325052747/https://www.seattlepi.com/news/article/Exploring-the-border-at-Blaine-U-S-Canada-1300963.php | dead-url = no }}</ref>

第零大道西端始于[[和平拱门国际公园|和平拱门国际公园]]，向正东延伸{{convert|28.9|km|mi}}，中途在太平洋公路边境口岸（{{lang|en|Pacific Highway Border Crossing}}）和林登-阿尔德格罗夫边境口岸（{{lang|en|Lynden–Aldergrove Border Crossing}}）两处不连续。在部分路段，第零大道和美国一侧的边界路（{{lang|en|Boundary Road}}）隔着边界并行大约1.5英里，沿途有许多用于边境监视的摄像头。第零大道和美国领土之间有一道人工壕沟，不过有若干小型桥梁让人穿越（例如在和平拱门国际公园这个缓冲区域，两国居民可以自由进入公园）。<ref name="clui">{{Cite web |url=http://www.clui.org/section/united-divide-a-linear-portrait-usacanada-border-5 |title=Chapter 6: Washington State |website=United Divide: A Linear Portrait of the USA/Canada Border |publisher=The Center for Land Use Interpretation |publication-date=Winter 2015 |access-date=2021-02-07 |archive-date=2017-11-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171114100046/http://www.clui.org/section/united-divide-a-linear-portrait-usacanada-border-5 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

尽管[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]后美加边界的监控有所加强，该路仍存在走私、非法越境活动。<ref>{{cite magazine|last1=MacDonald|first1=Jake|title=Smuggling on the Canada-U.S. border|url=http://www.canadiangeographic.ca/magazine/ja10/smuggler-inn.asp|magazine=Canadian Geographic|publisher=The Royal Canadian Geographical Society|access-date=8 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100710045056/http://www.canadiangeographic.ca/magazine/ja10/smuggler-inn.asp|archive-date=10 July 2010|year=2010}}</ref>2005年，在林登-阿尔德格罗夫边境口岸东侧的第零大道下方发现了走私用的隧道。一些寻求庇护的人也常试图从第零大道非法进入加拿大。<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/avenue-0-how-u-s-asylum-seekers-are-finding-their-way-to-british-columbia-1.4043406 | title = Avenue 0: How U.S. asylum seekers are finding their way to British Columbia | work = CBC News | date = 2017-03-28 | accessdate = 2021-02-06 | archive-date = 2020-11-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201112002740/https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/avenue-0-how-u-s-asylum-seekers-are-finding-their-way-to-british-columbia-1.4043406 | dead-url = no }}</ref>

